Photos.Caption: Here's me on a early Sunday morning!

Results.ReviewText: It saved my saturday!the usually running down to the local superstore dragging my kids behind me to find gold shining towards my trolley, I quickly transformed into a very jolly mood and fast walked to the coffee looking like a mad women to find Nescafé gold blend decafe I rushed home from the normal busy Saturday traffic and twisted the gold jar open the scent filled my room with magnificent freshly made coffee beans I was in ore and I splashed the beans into my warm milk and put my feet up as I switched of X factor!Nescafe i'd like to congratulate you for saving my Saturday!now all my family's drink i
Results.Title: Saved my Saturday!

ClientResponses.Response:
Hi,

We’re always wanting to improve the product for our loyal fans! After receiving feedback, we've added roast and ground coffee to our blend, to give it a richer aroma whilst maintaining the same smoothness. Watch this video to learn more: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aTUCiAvWyLg&index=22&list=PLBwKOSzTG9BZFv1nKqh8ZxxTOwJaeDaT

You could try NESCAFÉ Gold Crema as an alternative. This has a similar taste to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend but it's smoother and doesn't contain micro ground coffee.

We really value your feedback & appreciate you taking the time to let us know your thoughts. We've made a note of all your comments.

Results.ReviewText: I have been drinking the blue lidded coffee (black) for years and delighted with the taste. The new coffee has however, left me hugely disappointed. It does not have the same barista quality taste of the old recipe and the residue at the bottom of the cup after drinking suggests inferior grade coffee has been added. I also noticed the colour of the ground beans is much lighter in the gold top. I am desperate for an excellent cup of coffee and am looking for alternatives to Nescafé. How many of the reviewers who gave good reports had no experience of the blue top I wonder?
Results.Title: New, improved - you must be joking

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks for getting in touch. We have changed the packaging to make it easier for consumers to find NESCAFÉ Gold Blend, we have changed the colour of the jar to brushed champagne gold. Each of them still have a coloured label on the front to ensure consumers can still find them in store. We really value your feedback & will be making a note of all your comments.

Results.ReviewText: I've reviewed the normal new Gold Blend and I'll repeat what I said here - the new jar is awful for people with older hands.  Too big to hold easily and slippery. The lid is very hard to open.  Additional dislike is - why is the colour and labelling almost exactly the same as the caffienated?  The old jar had a blue lid and you could see at a glance which was which ( I use both in my home), but now the only difference is a slight variation in label colour and a tiny "decaff". Not easy to see if your eyesight isn't good.  Although Gold Blend decaff is probably the best decaff for me, I'm thinking of changing brands because of the jar design. My husband agrees with me. Also, the new coffee seems a bit bland and tasteless.
Results.Title: Not only a dreadful new jar, but why the colours?

Results.ReviewText: Great taste and full bodied, undoubtedly the best Decaff their is on the market. I've been using this brand for the last five years and it is has been consistently the best I've tried - the refills are well packaged and deliver just as well too.
Results.Title: The best Decaff their is!

Results.ReviewText: I was surprised when not only did the new jar of our favourite coffee change but the contents also.  Wished I had know as I  could have stocked up with the old style coffee.  Now I need to put more coffee into the cup to get the flavour but it leaves a bitter after taste, not such a great aroma too.  Not a fan of the grounds because if I wanted ground coffee I wouldn't be buying freeze dried instant coffee.  Most disappointed.  It is also hard to distinguish between each type of coffee (no buying it whilst half asleep)
Results.Title: New NESCAFÉ GOLD BLEND Decaff

Results.ReviewText: I bought a jar of this coffee during a promotion and since then have been enjoying this drink every day. I add coffee mate to make it taste even smoother and creamier, with a small spoon of honey. It really is delicious and I look forward to this lovely warming and comforting drink. Perfect for a cosy night in with the woodburner on.
Results.Title: smooth and comforting

Results.ReviewText: My sister visits us about twice a year from the States and her preference is decaff coffee. Her last visit was during the mid-term break just gone and so I had to stock up on the decaff coffee (as I dont usually buy decaff). I always buy Nescafe Gold blend so I bought the decaff blend for her. So while she was here, I mixed up the 2 mugs of coffee and she got mine and I got hers. After a while I noticed that she was a bit giddy and although she can sometimes be a bit giddy it was only when I went back out to the kitchen that I realised that I had given her my mug  - and I had the decaff. And you know what??? I never noticed the difference in taste - it was just like the real thing - what a welcome surprise and one converted customer. Well done!
Results.Title: Tastes just like the real thing!

Results.ReviewText: I have been buying this coffee for years.. It has a well rounded 'proper' coffee taste, by that I mean you can taste the full coffee aroma which is somewhat lacking in other  decaff coffees. You only need one rounded teaspoon per mug. It is slightly more expensive than some but certainly worth paying extra for. It makes a delish coffee & walnut cake too - Coffee and cake - mmmmmmm
Results.Title: Pleasant Well Rounded Brew

Results.ReviewText: I having been buying gold blend since the 1970’s when my friend introduced it to me. I take my coffee black with no sugar or sweetener. I was always very happy with the smooth rich blend. A few years later, I found I was having trouble sleeping and someone suggested that I might be having too much caffeine. I’ll try gold blend decaff I thought. I never saw the join! The aroma as I tore open the gold foil was the same, the taste was the same. I could now enjoy the rich roast of gold blend without the caffeine. And did I sleep better? Yes I certainly did! No more trouble! I’m still using gold blend decaff and I can’t ever see me going for anything else. I almost want to buy a new jar all the time just to smell that rich roast every time! Thank you Nescafé!
Results.Title: What a great blend

ClientResponses.Response: Hey, it's sad to hear that you're not happy with the new recipe but thank you very much for letting us know! We really value your feedback.

Results.ReviewText: I have drank gold blend de caff for several years, I love it. Recently it has chanfed.  I don't like the new coffee which apparently has coffee grounds in it to give it a richer taste, these are obvious and leave residue in the cup which is evident while you are drinking it,  it just puts me off  the coffee. Very sad I loved it before the change.
Results.Title: Prefer the old style

Results.ReviewText: bought this the other week and it was lovely. Tasty decaff for those of us who are intolerant of caffeine. Has no weird aftertaste that some brands have. Friends liked it too and were unaware it had no caffeine. Great for those morning wake up drinks without the buzz. Quality coffee at a great price, Love the shape of the jar too its narrower circumference made it feel extra special in my hands. i drink mine black but it is also good with a cream floater on top and a drop of brandy for the chilly evenings after dinner.
Results.Title: decaff

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, the residue you can see at the bottom of your cup is micro ground coffee that was added to NESCAFÉ Gold Blend during the recent change. This is non-soluble coffee and gives you a similar experience to that of a barista made coffee! Thank you very much for taking the time to get in touch & let us know what you think of the new recipe. It's sad to hear you're not a fan but we appreciate your feedback!

Results.ReviewText: I have been a Nescafe Gold Blend Decaff coffee drinker for too many years to remember and disappointed since your new Decaff coffee came on the market as it leaves a residue of coffee on the sides of a mug/cup and also in the bottom of the mug/cup which isn't very nice.  It also doesn't taste as good.
Results.Title: Disappointed

Results.ReviewText: I bought this on a whim as I was looking for something that was better than the standard 'work issue' coffee.  I was so glad I did. It is rich, smooth and goes down a treat - and the fact I have to hide it speaks volumes!
Results.Title: Rich and smooth

Results.ReviewText: I sometimes find that coffee can be quite acidic so I thought that I would try decaf coffee. I have heard good things about Nescafe Gold Blend and remember the couple from the advert years ago (showing my age now!) So, I decided to give it a go and wouldn't go back now. I like my coffee black so the Nescafe aroma just floods the room, unmarred by milk or sugar. The lack of caffeine means that I can drink as much as I like, without feeling guilty. Definitely my coffee of choice now!
Results.Title: Smooth and tasty coffee

Results.ReviewText: OK , I admit it it, I'm getting older and coffee keeps me awake if I drink it after my dinner.  But I still love the taste.  That's when Nescafe Gold Blend Decaff comes to the rescue!  I can drink it without wondering if I'll  get to sleep at night and at the same time I don't have to compromise on taste! "Rich and Smooth" are good descriptions of this blend.  A drop of milk and a bit of sugar turns my Nescafe Gold into a perfect caramel colour that goes down as silky as it looks!
Results.Title: When I crave the coffee but not the caffeine!

Results.ReviewText: Both my mum and I started to drink decaff for later in the day or evening coffee. We've tried a few different brands, but the Nescafé Gold Blend Decaff has been the best by far it doesn't taste to different to the more caffeinated coffee which is perfect for us. We also cheekily use it to make 'Coffee Martinis' as if used espresso we would be wired come bedtime and the quality and taste of this coffee is perfect for the cocktails. Would recommend trying this product well worth it.
Results.Title: Perfect for cuppa's later in the day

Results.ReviewText:
There are only so many ways you can re-invent the wheel (coffee) and in the past 50 years I think I've seen and tasted all of them.
I'm not going to go all mushy and say that this is the best incarnation of instant coffee in the world.
 But it takes a lot of beating with its rich and full bodied flavour and a pleasant after taste.
If you are going to buy De-café coffee then I would consider buying this one .
Again not the cheapest on the market but you get what you pay for.
Results.Title: Wot Not another variation on coffee!!!!!

Results.ReviewText: A soothing nightcap,something to send me off to bed happy but tasty and with a bit of night bite..just right.
Results.Title: My night time tipple of choice.

Results.ReviewText: Really enjoyed the taste and smell of this Nescafe Gold Decaff.  Will certainly buy again.
Results.Title: Great tasting coffee

Results.ReviewText: The number one decaf coffee, all the taste and flavour of Nescafe Gold Blend.
Results.Title: Taste the difference "not"

Results.ReviewText: Dont like this now you've changed it but used to love it
Results.Title: Not a good change

Results.ReviewText: I brought this product last week as i am very fussy about coffee and normally only ever drink lattes. I find most instant coffees very strong tasting and leave a nasty bitter taste in my mouth. This blend was fab, no nasty after taste and as it really is smooth it tasted great. This is just the type of coffee a busy mum like me needs to get me ready for the day ahead. I found it very pleasant and love the fresh coffee smell that lingers behind.
Results.Title: Tastes great

Results.ReviewText: I bought this for the first time about a year ago after Looking for a nice smooth tasting decaff coffee and this was just perfect the quality is the best instant coffee I have had and it’s great value for money the packaging makes it look much more expensive than it cost, A jar of this usually last me a month, but for those who use more when this is on offer I would recommend stocking up as it’s a great saving if you buy more than one a month.
Results.Title: Smooth Tasting Decaff Coffee

Results.ReviewText: you think coffee is coffee?  think again wth this product. wow! it has a real taste of the plantation, of the beans and the love of the grower all in one. when relaxing and sipping this you can easliy be transported to the fields, the sunshine  --and rain required-  that make this so good. ok siometimes it a rushed drink at a busy time but tey to relax and take the time to really appreciate s[pace and the TASTE of something special
Results.Title: satisfyingly  smooth taste

Results.ReviewText: My instant coffee of choice is regular Gold Blend, but I was finding those late night drinks were beginning to keep me awake. I'd tried decaff versions of coffee years ago and always found them somewhat lacking, but decided to give the Gold Blend version a try. To my surprise it tastes just as good as the caffeinated one! Doesn't keep me awake, so not my choice for an early morning kickstart, but excellent for late evening.
Results.Title: Great taste!

Results.ReviewText:
I made the choice to change to decaffinated coffee for health reasons, but found that all the decaf's I have had do not match in flavour or strength of caffinated brands. 
That is until i recently purchased Nescafe Gold Blend Decaff. It has a rich full bodied taste and a strong  flavour that makes me feel like i am drinking a real cup of coffee. I will be buying this coffee from now on and fully recommend it.
Results.Title: The first full flavour decaff i have tasted!

Results.ReviewText: We were offered a taster of this Coffee ( decaf)in Sainsbury's & absolutely fell in love with it. It's everything we want & need from a coffee . Normally instant decaf coffee, is weak, insipid & can be bitter, but this one tasted like normal coffee, & was just as good as the ground decafe we usually buy. Would recommend this coffee 100% & if the normal type is as good as the decaf, it's a win win for everyone.
Results.Title: Fantabulous

Results.ReviewText: I bought this coffee last week and I was pleasantly surprised at how good it tasted. I wouldn't be able to tell the difference between this Decaff version and the original  Nescafe blend. It tastes so smooth but also has the rich taste that a coffee should. The blend is very well balanced. This coffee is of very high quality and also good value for money. A great tasting coffee without the caffeine. Perfect
Results.Title: The best Decaff blend

Results.ReviewText: Great tasting decaff coffee. My Mother in Law introduced me to it as she has tried lots of decaff coffee over the years (including some very expensive upmarket brands!) and she reckons this is the best on the market. It's kind of creamy but rich tasting, and delicious first thing in a morning with a danish pastry! Yum xx I took it away on holiday with me last year and a member of staff bought it off me!!
Results.Title: Great tasing decaff coffee

Results.ReviewText:
I tried this out as I am addicted to coffee and wanted to keep to decaffeinated.  To my surprise and delight this was really good.   It tasted like most of Nescafe's coffees in that the strength was not weakened by the fact that it is decaffeinated.
It was a truly delightful and tasteful experience and i will be purchasing this again without a doubt.  it has become my regular coffee. Thank you Nescafe.
Results.Title: Best Decaf Coffee Around
